<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-29T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-29T03:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851<gloss target="#t_G1">G</gloss>.01/11–2949: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Saigon</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Abbott</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-29T16:00:00+08:00">November 29, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>416. Despatch from Vientiane announces that the Laos National
                                Assembly ratified Franco-Laotian treaty<note n="1" xml:id="d81fn1">See telegram 2904, July 20, 10 a. m., <ref target="#pg_68">p.
                                        68</ref>.</note> by 24 votes to 6 with two members absent.
                                Communiqué adds six negative votes represented opposition to
                                government and not to treaty. Prime Minister Bonn Gum arrived Saigon
                                yesterday to discuss organization joint committee for implementation
                                treaty.</p>
                            <p>Department pass Paris,<note n="2" xml:id="d81fn2">This was done the
                                    same day.</note> pouched Hanoi.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Abbott</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>